    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-28T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="39"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Billier</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-28T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>After immediate careful review of records relative thereto, consult Manager
                    Hussey of the Central &amp; South American Telegraph Co. regarding latest
                    contention of Argentine Director General of Telegraphs relative to annulment of
                    company’s concession of June 22, 1885, and thereupon reiterate to the Argentine
                    Government the desire of this Government that the contract be respected and
                    remind them of the value that it attaches to this important factor in the union
                    of the continents.</p>
                <p>If necessary communicate and cooperate by cable with Embassy at Rio de Janeiro.
                    …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
